ame": "context", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "grid", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "gridlines", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ticks", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "spines", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "fscale", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "figsize", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["main function for styling matplotlib according to theme\n\n::Arguments::\n\n: theme (str): 'oceans16', 'grade3', 'chesterish', 'onedork', 'monokai', 'solarizedl', 'solarizedd'. If no theme name supplied the currently installed notebook theme will be used.\n\n  context (str): 'paper' (Default), 'notebook', 'talk', or 'poster'\n\n  grid (bool): removes axis grid lines if False\n\n  gridlines (str): set grid linestyle (e.g., '--' for dashed grid)\n\n  ticks (bool): make major x and y ticks visible\n\n  spines (bool): removes x (bottom) and y (left) axis spines if False\n\n  fscale (float): scale font size for axes labels, legend, etc.\n\n  figsize (tuple): default figure size of matplotlib figures\n"]}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.set_style", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "rcdict", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "theme", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "grid", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "gridlines", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ticks", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "spines", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This code has been modified from seaborn.rcmod.set_style()\n\\::Arguments:\n\n```\nrcdict (str): dict of \"context\" properties (filled by set_context())\ntheme (str): name of theme to use when setting color properties\ngrid (bool): turns off axis grid if False (default: True)\nticks (bool): removes x,y axis ticks if True (default: False)\nspines (bool): removes axis spines if False (default: True)\n```\n"]}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.set_context", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "context", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "fscale", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "figsize", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Most of this code has been copied/modified from seaborn.rcmod.plotting_context()\n\\::Arguments:\n\n```\ncontext (str): 'paper', 'notebook', 'talk', or 'poster'\nfscale (float): font-size scalar applied to axes ticks, legend, labels, etc.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.figsize", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "aspect", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["manually set the default figure size of plots\n\\::Arguments:\n\n```\nx (float): x-axis size\ny (float): y-axis size\naspect (float): aspect ratio scalar\n```\n"]}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.get_theme_style", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "theme", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["read-in theme style info and populate styleMap (dict of with mpl.rcParams)\nand clist (list of hex codes passed to color cylcler)\n\\::Arguments:\n\n```\ntheme (str): theme name\n```\n\n::Returns::\n\n: styleMap (dict): dict containing theme-specific colors for figure properties\n  clist (list): list of colors to replace mpl's default color_cycle\n"]}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.get_default_jtstyle", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.get_color_list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.reset", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["full reset of matplotlib default style and colors\n    "]}], "variables": [{"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.jupyter_custom", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "jupyterthemes.jtplot.package_dir", "type": null